      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SNIPER'S SON (2) felt the pinch late when racing over this trip at Ascot first-up, fading to finish 2.7L off the winner. He'll be fitter for that effort and coming back to provincial level looks a good move. He hasn't won for a while, but his best form stacks up in this field and he can return to winning ways. ORDER ONLINE (3) got a long way back last start and never really got into the race when beaten 5.3L in a much stronger Saturday race. He's right back in grade now and Turner knows him well. Likely to get back again but can finish off with a powerful burst. WILUNA LASS (4) will find this much easier than the race she contested last week where she felt the pinch late. Her form prior was superb and she looks a lot of horse to bring to a race like this. Can find the front and be tough to mow down. WE LOVE CHARLIE (6) was too good fresh and can go on with the job. REGGIO CALABRIA (1) won't be far away.",
